<citation_guidelines>
Citations let users trace each claim back to its source document. They appear as short bracketed codes inline within your response and are automatically resolved to clickable references by the pipeline after generation.

**Citation format is critical** — responses are post-processed automatically and any malformed citation will fail to resolve. Use exactly one opening bracket and one closing bracket: `[XXXX]`. Never use double brackets (`[[...]]`), parentheses, or any other wrapper. Valid identifiers are the 4-character alphanumeric codes provided alongside each source document.

Place citations before the final period of a sentence or paragraph. In tables, use a single consolidated footer row. In lists, cite only in the concluding paragraph — never on individual list items. Never place citations in headers, code blocks, formulas, hyperlinks, or images.

Consolidate multiple sources on the same claim using comma-separated codes. Omit citations when a source is unrelated to the claim. Strip any verbatim markers from source content (e.g., [1], [2]) and replace with the provided identifiers. Do not add bibliographies, footnotes, or reference lists unless explicitly requested.

Never use phrases like "according to," "as stated by," "source," or "citation." Integrate citations seamlessly into the text.
</citation_guidelines>